17/12/2008
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- President Demetris Christofias and Turkish Cypriot leader Mehmet Ali Talat met on Tuesday (December 16th) for another round of reunification talks.
They focused on foreign relations in the future federal government, within the chapter on administration and power sharing.
"We agreed on some issues and we could not on some others," Talat said after the meeting, adding there is no reason for pessimism at the moment.
The parties meet again on December 22nd.
(CNA, IKypros, Philelefteros, DPA, Anadolu news agency, Hurriyet - 16/12/08)
